## Q11 — Atfiyyash on the creation of Adam (Q 2:30–39)

### Methodological caveat

**Significant retrieval failure.** The principal online hosts of *Himyān al-Zād ilā Dār al-Maʿād* and *Taysīr al-Tafsīr* — altafsir.com and greattafsirs.com (both Aal al-Bayt Institute) — returned bot-blocked responses on direct fetch attempts. The Internet Archive scan of *Himyān al-Zād* (haiamayan_azad_opt) exists in 20 part-volume PDFs but specific folio-text was not extracted. **Most of (a)–(f) below relies on snippet-level evidence and methodological inference. One direct verbatim retrieval was achieved: Atfiyyash on Q 17:64.** No Arabic has been fabricated. A user with a normal browser can recover verbatim text from `altafsir.com/Tafasir.asp?tMadhNo=6&tTafsirNo=49&tSoraNo=2&tAyahNo=30` (Himyān) and `tMadhNo=9&tTafsirNo=50` (Taysīr).

**Editions confirmed to exist.** *Himyān al-Zād ilā Dār al-Maʿād*, Muḥammad b. Yūsuf Aṭfayyish (Qutb al-Aʾimma, d. 1332/1914), first printed Zanzibar c. 1350 AH; reprinted Muscat, Wizārat al-Turāth al-Qawmī wa-l-Thaqāfī (Oman); Internet Archive 20-part scan. *Taysīr al-Tafsīr*, Muscat, Wizārat al-Turāth, 1406/1986, 17 vols.; Internet Archive identifier `tiser_alTafser`.

### (a) Full commentary on Q 2:30–39

**Verbatim retrieval from this session: NULL.** From paratextual evidence (the alsaidia.com bibliographic entry and ASJP/cerist.dz study of Aṭfayyish's method in Sūrat al-Baqara as *anmūdhaj*), Aṭfayyish treats the Adam pericope at length with linguistic/grammatical analysis (iʿrāb of *idh*, *jāʿil*, *khalīfa*), citation and selective rebuttal of Zamakhsharī (*jār Allāh*) and Bayḍāwī (*al-qāḍī*), and inclusion of Isrāʾīliyyāt that he sometimes critiques. *Himyān al-Zād* vol. 2 covers Baqara 1–141; *Taysīr al-Tafsīr* vol. 1 covers Fātiḥa and early Baqara. **Confidence: L** verbatim; **M** methodological.

### (b) "Innī jāʿilun fī al-arḍi khalīfah"

Direct Atfiyyash verbatim: NULL. The Ibadi exegetical field within which he writes canvasses three classical options: *(i)* deputy/vicegerent of God enforcing His decrees, *(ii)* successor to prior earth-dwellers (jinn / Banū al-Jānn), *(iii)* a people succeeding one another generation by generation. Given Aṭfayyish's method (multiple wujūh with arbitrated preference) and his documented engagement with the Ibadi exegete al-Hawwārī (who preserves the Jinn-pre-Adamic strand), it is highly likely he presents both (i) and (ii) as compatible. **Confidence: L verbatim; M doctrinal inference.**

### (c) "Wa-ʿallama Ādama al-asmāʾa kullahā"

Direct Atfiyyash verbatim: NULL. The standard option-set is: names of *all things* (Ibn ʿAbbās); names of the *angels* (al-Rabīʿ in one report); names of his *descendants* (ʿAbd al-Raḥmān b. Zayd); names of *stars* (Ḥumayd al-Shāmī); the *divine names* (Sufi/esoteric reading, Ibn ʿArabī, al-Qushayrī). Given Atfiyyash's philological-Zamakhsharian register and his demonstrated distance from extreme bāṭinī readings, the predicted preference is the broad "essences and acts of things" (ذوات الأشياء وأفعالها). **Confidence: L verbatim; M doctrinal inference.**

### (d) Nafkha / rūḥ (Q 15:29, 38:72, 32:9)

Direct Atfiyyash verbatim at these verses: NULL. The Ibadi kalām framework — which Aṭfayyish embodies at its 19th-c. peak — overwhelmingly treats *min rūḥī* as **iḍāfat tashrīf** (possessive of honorific attribution), exactly parallel to *nāqat Allāh* and *bayt Allāh*. The rūḥ is *jism laṭīf makhlūq* (a created subtle body), honorifically ascribed to God, not an emanation of His essence. Predicted gloss: «أجريت فيه روحاً خلقتها وأضفتها إلى نفسي تشريفاً». This rules out any "spark of divine essence" reading while preserving nafkha as the unique act that ontologically distinguishes Adam from prior earth-dwellers and from angels — i.e., as the basis for being taught the asmāʾ and meriting prostration.

**Cross-reference.** This is the configuration directly relevant to the project's "nafkha = distinguishing human capacity" frame. **Confidence: L verbatim; M doctrinal.**

